MESSAGE.value: Adding word embedding features to both craigslist and sentiment models. Need to double check that sentiment makes sense, then launch against real humans.
Refactored the gameplaying section and wrote some intro docs.
Further enriching the readme.
Notes on budget
Added mechanism for sending tutorials to the prospective workers. Need to write front-end. Should probably pay down some technical debt before writing anything more elaborate.
Front-end is configured to allow pushing tutorials to the humans before they get started, so hopefully it will be possible to train them to reasonable performance.
Tweaking front-end to improve styling and fix minor behavior glitches.
More fine-tuning of interface, removing the showing of tutorial if no tutorial is specified.
Started working on Expected-Utility gameplayer.
Changed the testWithRealHumans to only wait for 1 person, which makes demos a lot easier.
Added WaitForTime move.
Threading a bunch of useful information about human predictions collected into the analysis. Now just need to write it.
Added a huge pile of analysis code for visualizing the performance of HCUs.
Dumping the output guesses as they are made by humans. Still need to write tutorials for CoNLL before I can actually launch these stupid tasks.
Making minor piping changes to facciliate writing logs of decision making behavior.
Added support for YAML tutorial, also added intro slide and cheat-sheet.
Getting everything all buttoned up. Still need to fix turn-in button, but otherwise we are ready to go with NER. Scary stuff.
Final idiot check passed. Gonna try a real run.
Minorly fixing bugs and removing issues.
Seem to have most bugs worked out. Ready for another run, I think.
Simulations now draw samples from the true distribution of tired turkers. This means that we're going to get correct, if pessimistic, results.
CRF now adds human observation factors based on observed human distribution. Engine has access to both error and delay distributions, which are configurable. Refactored distribution locations.
Added an overall F1 and per class F1 to get a better handle on performance.
Making ThresholdHeuristic much more aggressive, running with a huge pool of workers, seeing what happens.
Added cacheing, stubbed out MCTS, etc
